Amnesty to Be Granted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 12 (KCNA) -- A decree of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea was promulgated to grant amnesty on the occasion of the 60th anniversaries of the Workers' Party of Korea and the liberation of Korea.
 The decree dated August 11 says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the army and the people of the DPRK will celebrate with splendor the 60th anniversaries of the WPK and Korea's liberation on the road of the fruitful drive to glorify the era of the Songun revolution under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il.
 The two anniversaries will mark the noteworthy political events as they will glorify the undying feats performed President Kim Il Sung and the WPK in building the Party and carrying out the revolutionary cause of Juche and the human cause of independence and powerfully demonstrate the might of the single-minded unity of the Party, the army and the people rallied close around the headquarters of the revolution and the spirit of Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Presidium of the SPA of the DPRK decides as follows in order to glorify the two anniversaries as grand political festivals and implement to the letter the benevolent politics, the all-embracing politics of the Party, true to the lifetime intention and cause of Kim Il Sung: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
1. Amnesty shall be granted on the occasion of the 60th anniversaries of the WPK and the liberation of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Amnesty shall be proclaimed from September 1, Juche 94 (2005). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 2. The Cabinet and relevant institutions shall take measures to ensure that those who are to be set free on pardon settle down in their work.

Anniversary of Korea's Liberation Celebrated Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 12 (KCNA) -- A meeting took place in Moscow on August 9 under the sponsorship of the Russian public circles on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the liberation of Korea.
 Vladimir Tolstikov, chairman of the Russian Association for Friendship and Cultural Cooperation with the DPRK, made an opening address at the meeting, which was followed by a report of Academician Mikhail Tsitarenko, director of the Institute of the Far East of the Russian Academy of Sciences. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter said that Korean friends and public figures in Russia are significantly marking the 60th anniversary of the liberation of Korea. They regard this historic day as a common holiday, he noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung wisely led the anti-Japanese war of the Korean people and liberated Korea, thus emerging one of the greatest politicians of the world.
 After liberation the President led the building of a new democratic state and the Fatherland Liberation War to victory and wisely steered the postwar rehabilitation and construction and socialist construction, thereby bringing about unprecedentedly great political and socio-economic changes. He is, indeed, the benefactor of the liberation for the Korean people, the sun of the nation and the founder of socialist Korea.
 Since 2000 the bilateral relations have grown stronger in all fields than ever before. Russia welcomes the positive developments in the situation on the Korean Peninsula.
 Branding the U.S. military presence in south Korea as an anachronistic act dating back to the Cold War era, he noted Russia has consistently held that the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula be settled politically and diplomatically and the peninsula be denuclearized. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Congratulatory messages to leader Kim Jong Il from various organizations of Russia were adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a meeting and a seminar were held in Democratic Congo and France and a meeting and a film show in Bangladesh and Nepal on the same occasion.

Ten-day Film Show Opens
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 12 (KCNA) -- A ceremony of opening the ten-day film show to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the liberation of Korea was held at the People's Palace of Culture here on August 11.
 Present were Jong Ha Chol, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, officials concerned, creators and artistes of the moviedom and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minister of Culture Choe Ik Gyu made an opening address at the ceremony. Then, the participants saw a documentary film "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Jong Il Gives On-site Guidance to the Work of Different Fields" (January-May, Juche 94) and a newly-released feature film "A Girl in Valley with Springs." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Screened at cinemas and houses of culture across the country during the film show will be documentaries and feature films dealing with the brilliant revolutionary life and undying feats of President Kim Il Sung and the wise leadership of  Kim Jong Il who is carrying forward and accomplishing the revolutionary cause of Juche started on Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are documentaries "The Leader Is the Great Father of Our People," "The Fatherly Leader among Anti-Japanese Revolutionary Fighters" and "The Fatherly Leader among Officials," which impressively show the revolutionary history of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are also documentaries "To Hold the Fatherly Leader in Higher Esteem," "Under the Care of the Great Brilliant Commander" and "Effecting a Great Turn with Songun Revolutionary Leadership," which show the great revolutionary history of Kim Jong Il.
 Among the feature films are "Star of Korea," "The Sun of the Nation" and "The Forest Sways," which depict the glorious revolutionary history of the President who devoted his whole life to the liberation of the country and its prosperity and development and the revolutionary feats of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Besides, there are "Five Guerrilla Brothers," "Rhododendron," "Wolmi Island," "My Happiness," "Airman Kil Yong Jo," "Legacy" and other feature films reflecting the heroic feats performed by the army and people of the DPRK in the annals of the Korean revolution as well as their noble mental world.

Appeal to World People
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 12 (KCNA) -- An appeal to the world people for building an independent, peaceful and friendly, new world was adopted at the meeting held on Thursday to watch the sunrise over Mt. Paektu with an attendance of the participants in the Meeting Dedicated to the Great Persons of Mt. Paektu.
 In the appeal representatives of international democratic organizations and friendship and solidarity organizations of different countries stressed the need to know better about the revolutionary life of the three generals of Mt. Paektu and conduct more brisk activities to introduce the great feats performed by them in accomplishing the human cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also called upon the progressive organizations and personages of all countries to add fuel to the flames of the international solidarity movement for supporting the Korean people in their Songun cause to check the imperialists' anachronistic ambition for world supremacy and gangster-like state terrorism and defend justice and peace.
 The appeal said that the peace-loving people and progressive figures from all walks of life in all countries should have a good understanding of all the peaceful stand and policies of the DPRK for the reunification of the country and the regional security and conduct more vigorous activities for supporting them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It called for extending full support to the Korean people in the tireless struggle to achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country by the concerted efforts of the whole nation under the banner of the historic June 15 joint declaration.

Int'l Solidarity with Korean Youth Called For
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 12 (KCNA) -- An appeal was adopted at the international forum on solidarity with the Korean youth in their struggle for the independent reunification of their country held on Aug. 9 as part of the events of the 16th World Festival of Youth and Students now under way in Caracas.
 The appeal noted that the world progressive youth and students participating in the 16th WFYS express full support and solidarity with the youth and other people of Korea in their struggle to achieve the country's reunification by their concerted efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It hailed and supported the three principles for national reunification--independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity--, the 10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo laid down by President Kim Il Sung as the most fair and aboveboard and realistic programme for achieving Korea's reunification as early as possible and called for boosting the solidarity with the youth other people of Korea in their efforts to realize it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Welcoming and supporting the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration adopted in Pyongyang thanks to the noble patriotic will and bold decision of leader Kim Jong Il as a firm milestone of Korea's reunification, the appeal called for sending full support and solidarity to the youth and other people of Korea in their efforts to successfully achieve the three forms of cooperation for national independence, peace against war and reunification and patriotism in the spirit of "By our nation itself" this year marking the fifth anniversary of the publication of the joint declaration and thus bring about a new phase for the independent reunification of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It sternly denounced the U.S. administration's anachronistic hostile policy towards the DPRK, a policy going against the process for the peaceful reunification of the Korean Peninsula and world peace, and called for launching a worldwide movement to force the Bush administration to unconditionally stop all the military exercises for aggression going on in and around the peninsula and withdraw its forces and destructive weapons from south Korea at once. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal strongly denounced the Bush administration's acts of sparking a new arms race and bringing the dark clouds of a nuclear war with a hue and cry over the "nuclear threat" from the DPRK as dangerous and inhumane criminal actions to upset the global strategic balance and carry out its strategy for world supremacy and stressed the need to intensify the struggle against these acts.

Japan Urged to Redeem Its Past Crimes
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 12 (KCNA) -- All the bitter grudge-bearing women of Korea will surely give vent to the pent-up hatred and resentment against Japan and force it to pay a dear price for its past crimes. 
 A spokeswoman for the Central Committee of the Korean Democratic Women's Union Friday declared this in a statement issued on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the defeat of the Japanese imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The misfortune and pain the Japanese imperialists imposed upon the women and other people of Korea for more than 40 years of their occupation of Korea were the most hideous and inhumane state-sponsored crimes that baffled human imagination and the crimes they have committed over the last 60 years since the liberation of Korea are unprecedentedly monstrous crimes, the statement noted, and continued:
 The barbaric sexual abuses the Japanese imperialists perpetrated against 200,000 Korean women after hurling them into the shambles of war of aggression are still touching off bitter indignation among the Koreans and other progressives.
 Nevertheless, Japan is seriously insulting the Korean women by describing the hair-raising sexual slavery forced upon the then Korean women as "prostitution."  It is brazen-faced enough to claim that the issue of the "comfort women" was a fabrication.
  It is also justifying visits to the "Yasukuni Shrine," painting its past war of aggression and crimes as "liberation" and "merits." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is a war criminal state which committed so many crimes against the world and humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It should redress its past crimes without fail, clearly understanding how the world approaches it and what strong will the Korean women have.

