&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 12 (KCNA) -- The grand mass gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang" has been successfully re-depicted to celebrate the 60th anniversaries of the Workers�f Party of Korea and the liberation of Korea.
 Its creators have paid deep attention to enhancing its ideological and artistic value in the re-depiction, with the result that they have already completed all acts and scenes and are now giving finishing touches to the preparation of the performance.
 The performers who are working people, youths, students and artistes have perfected rhythmic movements demanding a high sports and artistic skill through their repeated practice defying the unfavorable weather. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Schoolchildren have completed in three dimensional and rhythmic way such difficult scenes of the background as forest, flowers and fireworks, which demand congruence, discipline, swiftness and accuracy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Various kinds of settings have been prepared on a high level of artistic depiction. 
 The large slide projector operation apparatus, vast screen and other projecting and illuminating equipment have been tested to successfully ensure the performance of the work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 May Day Stadium, the venue of the performance, has been beautifully decorated.
 The presentation of Arirang, which well reflects history of the Arirang nation on a high sports and artistic standard to meet the ever-rising emotional requirement of the people, will brilliantly adorn the 60th anniversaries as a grand festival of victors.

Tributes to Fallen Soviet Soldiers Paid in Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 12 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the cemetery of fallen Soviet soldiers in Hungnam, South Hamgyong Province, the monument to the fallen soldiers of the Soviet army in Wonsan, Kangwon Province, the statue of the Soviet soldier in Nampho, South Phyongan Province, and the liberation tower in Haeju, South Hwanghae Province, on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the liberation of Korea.
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremonies were secretaries and concurrently vice-chairpersons of the above-said provincial people's committees and officials of the city people's committees, working people in cities and Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Andrei Karlov and embassy officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amidst the playing of wreath-laying music, wreaths, together with bouquets, were placed before the cemetery, monument, statue and the liberation tower in the name of power bodies, working people's organizations, people's security organs, universities and industrial establishments in the provinces and cities and the Russian ambassador and embassy officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbons of the wreaths were words "Glory to the fallen soldiers of the Soviet army!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants observed a moment's silence in memory of the soldiers of the Soviet army who fell in the battles for the liberation of Korea and looked round the cemetery, monument, statue and liberation tower.

Korean Farm Renamed DPRK-Belgium Friendship Farm
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 12 (KCNA) -- A ceremony of renaming the March 3 Farm the DPRK-Belgium Friendship Farm was held on the spot Friday.
 Present there were officials concerned and officials and agricultural workers of the farm. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were members of the visiting delegation of the Solidarity Committee "Korea Is One" of Belgium headed by its Secretary General Catherine Dijon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The farm was renamed the DPRK-Belgium Friendship Farm before speeches were made. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Aid materials sent by the solidarity committee were conveyed at the ceremony.
 Then the participants enjoyed an art performance given by schoolchildren and kindergarteners and exchanged conversations with farmers, deepening the friendship.
 The guests looked round a clinic, a kindergarten, houses and fields of the farm.
